                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d710">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">762.9411/125½: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Grew</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Tokyo</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-10-21T18:00:00+09:00"
                            >October 21, 1940—6 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received October 21—7:03 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1022. Japan’s treaty alliance with Germany and Italy was ratified by the Emperor
                    on October 19 and published in the <hi rend="italic">Gazette</hi> on October <pb
                        facs="0679" n="667" xml:id="pg_667"/> 21 in the Japanese language only. The
                    phraseology is the same as previously published in the press.<note n="83"
                        xml:id="d710fn83">The Department was informed on November 20, 23, and 24,
                        1940, that Hungary, Rumania, and Slovakia had adhered to the treaty.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Grew</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
